The paper deals with the capacity of a noisy channel, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves simulating protocols, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses lower bounds and the Shannon capacity, which are concepts in cryptography (cs.CR). The use of finite-state protocols suggests a connection to automata theory and formal languages (cs.DS). Finally, the paper's focus on simulating protocols over a channel suggests a connection to networking and communication (cs.NI).
